Class Node<L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • homework2.Node<L>

  • public class Node<L>
extends java.lang.Object
    A Node is an abstraction of a Bipartite Graph Node Element. As such, each Node has a color that can be either Black or White and it stores the information we want to represent using the bipartite graph nodes. It also contains information about its parents and its children. Thus, a typical Node has the properties {label, data, color, children, parents, childrenList, parentsList} A Node is immutable
